description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity is available for an occupational therapist who a passion for working with children and young people with severe and profound learning and physical disabilities to join our Special Schools Team at Sheffield Children&#39;s NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time temporary vacancy to cover a 12 month maternity leave from January/February 2021. The post will be based in two of the special schools in Sheffield, with some travelling for home visits and will involve working with children from 5-19 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have experience of working with children or young adults with neurodisabilities and would like an opportunity to increase your skills and experience, you would be joining a friendly and highly expereinced team of physios and OTs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need enthusiasm, flexiblity, good basic OT skills and knowledge, excellent communication and team working skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like you, we look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
